NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_pim_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT, IxNetwork-NGPF

This procedure will configure PIM SM interface.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_pim_config

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

-port_handle

Supported platforms Details

DESCRIPTION

The port on which the PIM-SM neighbor pair is to be created.

DEFAULT

 None

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M] , IxOS/IxNetwork-FT [M]

DESCRIPTION

This option defines the action to be taken. Limitations: for modify mode, the following options cannot be changed: router_id, dr_priority, join_prune_holdtime, and join_prune_interval. Valid options are:create (DEFAULT)modifydeletedisableenableenable_alldisable_all

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

This option defines the action to be taken. Limitations: for modify mode, the following options cannot be changed: router_id, dr_priority, join_prune_holdtime, and join_prune_interval. Valid options are: create (DEFAULT) modify delete disable enable

Valid options are:

-interface_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

A handle or list of the handles that are returned from the interface_config call. These provide a direct link to an already existing interface and supercede the use of the intf_ip_addr value.

DEFAULT

 None

-return_detailed_handles

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.

DEFAULT

0

-count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Number of PIM-SM sessions to create on the interface.If this parameter is 1 then the default behaviour of this function is to create a routerand add the interfaces to it. In this case the following parameters may be lists:interface_handle ip_version generation_id_mode hello_holdtime hello_interval prune_delay prune_delay_tbit override_interval bidir_capable send_generation_id prune_delay_enable neighbor_intf_ip_addr bootstrap_support_unicast bootstrap_enable bootstrap_hash_mask_len bootstrap_interval bootstrap_priority bootstrap_timeout (only IxTclNetwork api)

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Number of PIM-SM sessions to create on the interface. If this parameter is 1 then the default behaviour of this function is to create a router and add the interfaces to it. In this case the following parameters may be lists: interface_handle ip_version generation_id_mode hello_holdtime hello_interval prune_delay prune_delay_tbit override_interval bidir_capable send_generation_id prune_delay_enable neighbor_intf_ip_addr bootstrap_support_unicast bootstrap_enable bootstrap_hash_mask_len bootstrap_interval bootstrap_priority bootstrap_timeout (only IxTclNetwork api) (DEFAULT = 1)

DEFAULT

1

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

The period, in seconds, during which a router receiving a Join/Prune must keep the state alive. The default is 3 times the Join/Prune interval. If this value is 65536 (0xffff), then the timeout is infinite and if this value isi 0, the timeout is immediate.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

The period, in seconds, during which a router receiving a Join/Prune must keep the state alive. The default is 3 times the Join/Prune interval. If this value is 65536 (0xffff), then the timeout is infinite and if this value isi 0, the timeout is immediate. (DEFAULT = 180)

DEFAULT

180
